FIELD	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
The	O
present	O
invention	O
pertains	O
to	O
the	O
field	O
of	O
user	O
input	O
processing	O
and	O
correction	O
.	O
More	O
particularly	O
,	O
this	O
invention	O
relates	O
to	O
a	O
character-based	O
correction	O
arrangement	O
for	O
a	O
user	O
input	O
recognition	O
system	O
with	O
correction	O
propagation	O
.	O

BACKGROUND	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
Inputting	O
a	O
Chinese	O
character	O
by	O
means	O
of	O
keyboard	O
is	O
difficult	O
,	O
time-consuming	O
,	O
and	O
typically	O
requiring	O
extensive	O
training	O
in	O
input	O
methods	O
.	O
This	O
is	O
due	O
to	O
the	O
fact	O
that	O
the	O
Chinese	O
language	O
is	O
a	O
pictographic	O
language	O
and	O
has	O
more	O
than	O
several	O
thousand	O
different	O
characters	O
.	O
Since	O
one	O
use	O
of	O
speech	O
recognition	O
is	O
to	O
enter	O
large	O
amounts	O
of	O
text	O
into	O
a	O
computer	O
system	O
efficiently	O
,	O
it	O
is	O
advantageous	O
to	O
input	O
Chinese	O
text	O
using	O
speech	O
recognition	O
.	O

Speech	O
recognition	O
systems	O
inevitably	O
make	O
recognition	O
errors	O
.	O
Hence	O
,	O
it	O
is	O
necessary	O
to	O
employ	O
a	O
correction	O
system	O
in	O
the	O
speech	O
recognition	O
systems	O
.	O
In	O
this	O
case	O
,	O
the	O
computer	O
system	O
typically	O
displays	O
a	O
list	O
of	O
alternative	O
words	O
in	O
the	O
vocabulary	O
(	O
e.g.	O
,	O
an	O
active	O
lexicon	O
)	O
that	O
best	O
match	O
what	O
the	O
user	O
spoke	O
.	O
The	O
correction	O
schemes	O
in	O
prior	O
art	O
dictation	O
systems	O
(	O
or	O
programs	O
)	O
are	O
typically	O
tailored	O
for	O
word-based	O
languages	O
(	O
i	O
.	O
e	O
.	O
,	O
English	O
and	O
French	O
)	O
.	O
While	O
the	O
words	O
in	O
Western	O
languages	O
are	O
clearly	O
defined	O
by	O
blank	O
spaces	O
between	O
those	O
words	O
,	O
the	O
concept	O
of	O
a	O
"	O
word	O
"	O
for	O
the	O
Chinese	O
language	O
is	O
ambiguous	O
because	O
there	O
is	O
no	O
equivalent	O
word	O
separator	O
in	O
the	O
Chinese	O
language	O
.	O
This	O
typically	O
causes	O
correction	O
of	O
Chinese	O
text	O
to	O
be	O
difficult	O
when	O
a	O
prior	O
art	O
word-based	O
language	O
correction	O
scheme	O
is	O
employed	O
to	O
correct	O
the	O
Chinese	O
text	O
.	O

In	O
summary	O
,	O
because	O
a	O
Chinese	O
word	O
is	O
formed	O
by	O
one	O
or	O
a	O
number	O
of	O
characters	O
,	O
it	O
is	O
typically	O
unnatural	O
to	O
apply	O
a	O
word-based	O
language	O
correction	O
scheme	O
to	O
the	O
Chinese	O
language	O
.	O

SUMMARY	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
A	O
method	O
of	O
correcting	O
a	O
text	O
in	O
a	O
data	O
processing	O
system	O
is	O
described	O
.	O
One	O
of	O
the	O
features	O
of	O
the	O
method	O
of	O
the	O
present	O
invention	O
is	O
to	O
allow	O
correction	O
of	O
a	O
document	O
to	O
be	O
relatively	O
fast	O
and	O
effective	O
.	O

Another	O
feature	O
of	O
the	O
method	O
of	O
the	O
present	O
invention	O
is	O
to	O
provide	O
a	O
correction	O
system	O
that	O
allows	O
corrections	O
in	O
a	O
document	O
made	O
by	O
a	O
user	O
to	O
be	O
propagated	O
forward	O
in	O
the	O
document	O
such	O
that	O
the	O
document	O
is	O
corrected	O
by	O
the	O
system	O
in	O
accordance	O
with	O
the	O
portion	O
of	O
the	O
document	O
corrected	O
by	O
the	O
user	O
.	O

The	O
method	O
in	O
accordance	O
with	O
one	O
embodiment	O
of	O
the	O
invention	O
includes	O
the	O
step	O
of	O
locating	O
a	O
first	O
incorrect	O
character	O
in	O
the	O
text	O
.	O
A	O
character	O
list	O
of	O
alternative	O
characters	O
for	O
the	O
first	O
incorrect	O
character	O
is	O
then	O
shown	O
to	O
the	O
user	O
from	O
which	O
the	O
user	O
chooses	O
a	O
character	O
to	O
replace	O
the	O
first	O
incorrect	O
character	O
with	O
a	O
correct	O
character	O
from	O
the	O
character	O
list	O
.	O
As	O
an	O
alternative	O
to	O
the	O
character	O
list	O
,	O
the	O
user	O
may	O
input	O
a	O
correct	O
character	O
without	O
using	O
a	O
list	O
of	O
characters	O
,	O
such	O
as	O
the	O
character	O
list	O
.	O
The	O
change	O
of	O
the	O
first	O
incorrect	O
character	O
is	O
then	O
propagated	O
through	O
the	O
remainder	O
of	O
the	O
text	O
in	O
accordance	O
with	O
a	O
matching	O
score	O
and	O
a	O
language	O
probability	O
score	O
of	O
the	O
remainder	O
of	O
the	O
text	O
.	O
An	O
apparatus	O
which	O
corrects	O
text	O
in	O
a	O
data	O
processing	O
system	O
is	O
also	O
described	O
.	O

